nodes.title: Note: Color Correct
widgets_values:
You can change the settings above to whatever you prefer. At the current settings, it doesn't change anything.

I do recommend leaving the gamma setting at 1.0.

Raising gamma darkens the image, while lowering it brightens it.

The rest of the settings are straightforward with what they do IMO. Just imagine you are changing the settings on your monitor/tv.

nodes.title: Note: About Image Comparer and 2nd Pass
widgets_values:
Image Comparer:

These show the "before" image by default. Move your mouse cursor over the image from left to right to see the after result.

Why a 2nd pass?

This can help reduce artifacts/clean up the image before upscaling. 100% optional and NOT required. IMO this is more useful if you are going to be using a different sampler/scheduler after the initial image. In some cases, it can makes things worse so YMMV.

nodes.title: Note: FaceDetailer
widgets_values:
For information about the FaceDetailer parameters, go here and check section 5:

https://www.runcomfy.com/tutorials/face-detailer-comfyui-workflow-and-tutorial

Tips:

bbox_threshold is the setting to adjust if thing are/are not being detected. Higher = less sensitive. Lower = more sensitive.

My guide_size and max_size settings are probably higher than normal. If it's taking too long for you, you can try adjusting the max_size setting down.

My normal step count (20) is pretty high IMO. You can drop it to 10 or less probably and still get good results.

If you're getting weird results, try describing what is being detailed via prompts in the "wildcard spec" field on the FaceDetailer node.

FYI:

Sometimes the detection models will detect a face/eye/hand/etc that is not a face/eye/hand/etc.

Note: Global Sampler
widgets_values: This only partially works. If you pick a sampler or scheduler that is not compatible with all of the nodes in the workflow, it will throw an error.

nodes.title: Note: CFGZeroStar
widgets_values: Does not work with all models, but it's supposed to help your CFG work better pretty much.

nodes.title: Note: Ultimate SD Upscale
widgets_values:
For info:

https://github.com/ssitu/ComfyUI_UltimateSDUpscale

Parameter Info:

https://github.com/Coyote-A/ultimate-upscale-for-automatic1111/wiki/FAQ#parameters-descriptions

Tips:

You can drop the tile_padding to a lower number like 128 and USDU will work faster, but increases the chance of weird stuff happening. The bigger the tile_padding, the more USDU "looks" at while working.

My normal step count (25) is high, you can probably drop it to 10 or less depending on your sampler/scheduler/model.

FYI: Not all samplers/schedulers play nice with USDU.

Upscale Model:

You can use whatever you prefer. Some upscale models seem to have issues with USDU, so YMMV.

If you want the one I am using, you can get it here for free (as of Sep 4 2025) if you have a ko-fi account:

https://ko-fi.com/kim20913944/shop
